Linux User Management Tasks

Create a new user.
Set a password for a user.
Modify a user’s home directory and default shell.
Delete a user along with their home directory.
Create a new group.
Add a user to an existing group.
Remove a user from a group.
Delete a group from the system.
Change the ownership of a file or directory.
Modify file permissions for a user or group.
Grant a user sudo (administrative) privileges.
List all users in the system.
Check a user's groups and permissions.
Lock and unlock a user account.
Expire a user’s password to force a reset on next login.
chage -M to set Expire users password

Set an account expiration date for a user.
chage -E for date 

Disable a user account without deleting it.
View system login history and failed login attempts.
Create a new user with a specific UID and GID.
Assign a user to multiple groups.
